nce-learning/)\n    \n\n[Enterprise Works](/enterprise-works/)\n\n*   [Entrepreneur Support](/enterprise-works/entrepreneur-support/)\n*   [Business Services](/enterprise-works/business-services/)\n*   [Social Enterprise](/enterprise-works/social-enterprise/)\n*   [Research](/enterprise-works/research/)\n*   [Meaningful Business](/enterprise-works/meaningful-business-network/)\n*   [Events](/enterprise-works/events/)\n*   [A New Era for Female Entrepreneurship](/enterprise-works/new-era/)\n*   [News](/enterprise-works/news/)\n*   [Articles](/enterprise-works/articles/)\n*   [Enterprise Awards](/enterprise-works/university-of-york-enterprise-awards/)\n*   [Entrepreneurial Journeys](/enterprise-works/entrepreneurial-journeys/)\n*   [Business Advice](/enterprise-works/business-advice/)\n*   [Founder Advisory Board](/enterprise-works/founder-advisory-board/)\n*   [Enterprise Teaching and Learning](/enterprise-works/enterprise-teaching/)\n\n[Home](/)[Enterprise Works](/enterprise-works/)[A New Era for Female Entrepreneurship](/enterprise-works/new-era/)\n\n![](/media/enterprise-works/1739183425867.jpg)\n\n# A New Era for Female Entrepreneurship in York & North Yorkshire\n\n\"We have reached a tipping point where governments, business support organisations, and female entrepreneurs themselves realise the enormous value of female enterprise to the regional and national economy. It is vital for the future success of the region that we have a clear, data-driven understanding of the needs of this community, to ensure that we maximise our, and their, chances of success and drive inclusive growth for all.\"  \n_Professor Kiran Trehan, Pro-Vice-Chancellor for Enterprise, Partnerships and Engagement_\n\nThe University of York and the [Federation of Small Businesses (FSB)](https://www.fsb.org.uk/) have conducted research to understand the barriers faced by female founders in York and North Yorkshire. This research has reported on how women are overcoming social bias and barriers to business as well as what needs to be done to remove the necessity for continued gender equality conversations over the next decade. \n\nIn developing this report specifically for York & North Yorkshire, we hope to address the challenges unique to this region and co-create solution-based approaches.\n\n## Contact us\n\nWe’d be delighted to hear from you.\n\n*   [enterprise-works@york.ac.uk](mailto:enterprise-works@york.ac.uk)\n*   [+44 (0)1904 321420](tel:+441904 321420)\n*   [@UoYEntWorks](https://x.com/UoYEntWorks)\n*   [LinkedIn](https://www.linkedin.com/showcase/enterprise-works-at-the-university-of-york)\n\n## Key Findings\n\nWomen entrepreneurs are at the forefront of creating innovative solutions, generating employment, and spearheading sustainable development. Despite facing unique challenges, they demonstrate resilience, creativity, and an unwavering spirit that inspires us all. This report delves into the myriad factors influencing female entrepreneurship, offering valuable insights into the barriers they face, the strategies they employ, and the ecosystems that support their success.\n\n*   Download:  [New Era for female entrepreneurship in YNY - summary report (PDF ![](/media/global/icons/icon_pdf.gif), 3,514kb)](/media/enterprise-works/newerareport/New Era for female entreperneurship in YNY - summary report - Sep 24.pdf \"New Era for female entrepreneurship in YNY - summary report (opens in a new window)\")\n*   Find out more about the [New Era for Female entrepreneurship in York and North Yorkshire Pledge](https://cms.york.ac.uk/terminalfour/preview/1/en/304390)\n\n![People working](/media/enterprise-works/images/EJ and Advice banner 2.jpg)\n\n## Opportunity\n\n![A group of women](/media/enterprise-works/images/1 Women in enterprise.jpg)\n\n**York & North Yorkshire (YNY) stands to create up to 165,000 jobs and could add £2.6 billion to GVA by investing in female entrepreneurs in our region. The report identifies seven priority areas to better support existing and future female entrepreneurs across the region, including:**\n\n1.  Struggling with confidence.\n2.  Difficult pathways to self-employment.\n3.  Understanding and access to finance.\n4.  Understanding and investing in customer acquisition, retention and pricing\n5.  Quality and availability of various forms of local infrastructure.\n6.  Quality and availability of mentorship.\n7.  Managing business administration. \n\n## Breaking Barriers Podcast\n\n_Breaking Barriers_ is a podcast celebrating women entrepreneurs in York and North Yorkshire. Hosted by Andrea Morrison and produced by Enterprise Works, each episode shares stories, insights, and tools to inspire and support women building businesses across our region.\n\n![](https://i.ytimg.com/vi/gRVHqL01Y5s/sddefault.jpg)\n\nVideo\n\n### [Episode 1: “The Confidence Conundrum”](#uoy_modal_youtube_embed_1183080_1)\n\nIn our first episode, we're diving straight in to one of the biggest challenges for women in business in our region, lack of confidence. This episode explores some of the challenges female entrepreneurs face, and provides insight in to how to overcome them. We're joined by Professor Kiran Trehan and Katie Reeves, owner of Festive Green.\n\n[https://youtu.be/gRVHqL01Y5s](https://youtu.be/gRVHqL01Y5s)\n\n[](#)\n\n![](https://i.ytimg.com/vi/T4arCBfumv0/sddefault.jpg)\n\nVideo\n\n### [Episode 2: \"The Path to Self Employment\"](#uoy_modal_youtube_embed_1183080_2)\n\nIn this episode, we discuss inequality and caregiving expectations. We explore how systemic barriers, rigid workplaces, and gendered caregiving roles push women to build businesses on their own terms—while confronting the emotional toll and logistical maze of doing it all. We're joined by Valentina Hynes, SVH Inc and Emily Pickard, York Mumbler.\n\n[https://youtu.be/T4arCBfumv0](https://youtu.be/T4arCBfumv0)\n\n[](#)\n\n## 100 Voices\n\nOur 100 Voices campaign is a collective response to the research findings, a storytelling movement designed to raise the visibility of female entrepreneurs and ensure they are recognised, celebrated, and supported. Through this campaign, we will showcase the journeys, challenges, and successes of 100 women, highlighting the support available to female entrepreneurs and placing their stories at the heart of a regional shift toward inclusive business support, partnering with local business support from the Growth Hub and City of York Council.\n\n![](/media/enterprise-works/Untitled-design-12.webp)\n\nBlog post\n\n### [Sara Davies](https://alumnivoices.co.uk/2025/07/07/sara-davies-entrepreneur-being-myself-was-enough/)\n\n![](/media/enterprise-works/anna richey.webp)\n\nBlog post\n\n### [Two Chicks](https://alumnivoices.co.uk/2024/06/06/anna-richey-two-chicks-co-founder/)\n\n![](/media/enterprise-works/sarah perkins.webp)\n\nBlog post\n\n### [Sarah Parkins](https://alumnivoices.co.uk/2023/03/13/sarah-parkins-entrepreneur/)\n\n![](/media/enterprise-works/images/1.png)\n\nBlog post\n\n### [The Rose Press Garden](https://www.york.ac.uk/enterprise-works/entrepreneurial-journeys/lizzie-munson/)\n\n![](/media/enterprise-works/york-cocoa-house-jma-photography-5.jpg)\n\nBlog post\n\n### [York Cocoa Works](https://www.york.ac.uk/enterprise-works/meaningful-business-network/york-cocoa-works/)\n\n![](/media/enterprise-works/images/Bethan Vincent profile shot for web.jpg)\n\nBlog post\n\n### [Open Velocity](https://www.york.ac.uk/enterprise-works/entrepreneurial-journeys/bethan-vincent/)\n\n![](/media/enterprise-works/Untitled (96).jpeg)\n\nBlog post\n\n### [Tutor Fox](https://www.york.ac.uk/enterprise-works/university-of-york-innovate-york/innovate-york-case-studies/)\n\n![](/media/enterprise-works/images/2.png)\n\nBlog post\n\n### [SVH Inc](https://www.york.ac.uk/enterprise-works/entrepreneurial-journeys/valentina-hynes/)\n\n![](/media/enterprise-works/images/Untitled design (24).png)\n\nBlog post\n\n### [Myth Drinks](https://www.york.ac.uk/enterprise-works/university-of-york-innovate-york/innovate-york-case-studies/)\n\n![](/media/enterprise-works/chocandcofinal-102.webp)\n\nBlog post\n\n### [Chocolate & Co](https://www.york.ac.uk/enterprise-works/meaningful-business-network/chocolate-and-co/)\n\n![](/media/enterprise-works/images/Bethany.png)\n\nBlog post\n\n### [Experience Heritage](https://www.york.ac.uk/enterprise-works/entrepreneurial-journeys/bethany-watrous/)\n\n![](/media/enterprise-works/Cher Casey pic 4.jpg)\n\nBlog post\n\n### [The Mindful Organiser](https://www.york.ac.uk/enterprise-works/university-of-york-innovate-york/innovate-york-case-studies/)\n\n![](/media/enterprise-works/images/Katie Lingo-2998x2388.jpg)\n\nBlog post\n\n### [Katie Lingo](https://www.york.ac.uk/enterprise-works/entrepreneurial-journeys/katie-thompson/)\n\n![](/media/enterprise-works/youth 17.JPG)\n\nBlog post\n\n### [Door 84](https://www.york.ac.uk/enterprise-works/meaningful-business-network/door-84/)\n\n![](/media/enterprise-works/anne wyn-jones.jpg)\n\nBlog post\n\n### [Traydle](https://www.york.ac.uk/enterprise-works/entrepreneurial-journeys/anne-wyn-jones/)\n\n![](/media/enterprise-works/images/LucyLEAFPictures-73.JPG)\n\nBlog post\n\n### [LeaF Translations](https://www.york.ac.uk/enterprise-works/meaningful-business-network/leaf-translations/)\n\n![](/media/enterprise-works/images/Cooper King_Founders_Chris and Abbie_2.jpg)\n\nBlog post\n\n### [Cooper King Distillery](https://www.york.ac.uk/enterprise-works/meaningful-business-network/cooper-king/)\n\n![](/media/enterprise-works/Iris.png)\n\nVideo\n\n### [Iris Graphics](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1YNxwj3c1hI)\n\n![](/media/enterprise-works/Sarah .png)\n\nVideo\n\n### [Wild Bee Flower Farm](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=qOCMRlPPxfQ&t=2s)\n\n![](/media/enterprise-works/images/chaibike.jpg)\n\nBlog post\n\n### [Chai Bike](https://www.york.ac.uk/enterprise-works/entrepreneurial-journeys/sally-pierse/)\n\n![](/media/enterprise-works/images/Untitled design (25).png)\n\nBlog post\n\n### [VegoPak](https://www.york.ac.uk/enterprise-works/entrepreneurial-journeys/maisy-whitehead/)\n\n![](/media/enterprise-works/Untitled design (27).png)\n\nBlog post\n\n### [SealStop](https://www.york.ac.uk/enterprise-works/entrepreneurial-journeys/belle-richardson/)\n\n![](/media/enterprise-works/LOGO.png)\n\nBlog post\n\n### [The Recharge Hub](https://www.york.ac.uk/enterprise-works/entrepreneurial-journeys/recharge-hub/)\n\n![](/media/enterprise-works/IMG_0014-1024x683.jpg)\n\nBlog post\n\n### [Fabrication Crafts](https://ynygrowthhub.com/blog/news/fabrication-flourishes-with-support-from-city-of-york-council/)\n\n![](/media/enterprise-works/RachelBarber.jpg)\n\nBlog post\n\n### [Living4Moments](https://www.york.ac.uk/enterprise-works/entrepreneurial-journeys/living-4-moments)\n\n![](/media/enterprise-works/Untitled design (28).png)\n\nBlog post\n\n### [Community Bees](https://www.york.ac.uk/enterprise-works/entrepreneurial-journeys/community-bees/)\n\n![](/media/enterprise-works/website mixed media image size.png)\n\nBlog post\n\n### [Natalie McMillan](https://www.york.ac.uk/enterprise-works/entrepreneurial-journeys/natalie-mcmillan/)\n\n![](/media/enterprise-works/little seed field.png)\n\nBlog post\n\n### [Little Seed Field](https://ynygrowthhub.com/blog/case-studies/how-joanne-found-value-in-a-focused-business-vision/)\n\n![](/media/enterprise-works/hummingbird.jpg)\n\nBlog post\n\n### [Hummingbird Paper Co](https://ynygrowthhub.com/blog/case-studies/local-start-up-planner-business-benefits-from-500-seed-funding-thanks-to-innovation-supper/)\n\n![](/media/enterprise-works/website mixed media image size (1).png)\n\nBlog post\n\n### [OT4me](https://ynygrowthhub.com/blog/case-studies/rachel-derrys-journey-to-management-with-the-seventh-wave-programme/)\n\n![](/media/enterprise-works/website mixed media image size (2).png)\n\n### [Festive Green](https://www.york.ac.uk/enterprise-works/entrepreneurial-journeys/katie-reeves/)\n\n![](/media/enterprise-works/5253ff_3609c8b73cc4