      "content": "                         Launch of A New Era for Female Enterprise report in York and North Yorkshire | University of York posted on the topic | LinkedIn              \n\n  \n\nAgree & Join LinkedIn\n\nBy clicking Continue to join or sign in, you agree to LinkedIn’s [User Agreement](/legal/user-agreement?trk=linkedin-tc_auth-button_user-agreement), [Privacy Policy](/legal/privacy-policy?trk=linkedin-tc_auth-button_privacy-policy), and [Cookie Policy](/legal/cookie-policy?trk=linkedin-tc_auth-button_cookie-policy).\n\n[Skip to main content](#main-content)\n\n[LinkedIn](/?trk=public_post_nav-header-logo)\n\n*   [Top Content](https://www.linkedin.com/top-content?trk=public_post_guest_nav_menu_topContent)\n*   [People](https://www.linkedin.com/pub/dir/+/+?trk=public_post_guest_nav_menu_people)\n*   [Learning](https://www.linkedin.com/learning/search?trk=public_post_guest_nav_menu_learning)\n*   [Jobs](https://www.linkedin.com/jobs/search?trk=public_post_guest_nav_menu_jobs)\n*   [Games](https://www.linkedin.com/games?trk=public_post_guest_nav_menu_games)\n*   [Get the app](ms-windows-store://pdp/?ProductId=9WZDNCRFJ4Q7&mode=mini&cid=guest_nav_upsell&trk=public_post_guest_nav_menu_windows)\n\n[Sign in](https://www.linkedin.com/login?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww%2Elinkedin%2Ecom%2Fposts%2Funiofyork_building-a-new-era-for-female-entrepreneurship-activity-7394785371517132800-f79q&fromSignIn=true&trk=public_post_nav-header-signin) [Join now](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww%2Elinkedin%2Ecom%2Fposts%2Funiofyork_building-a-new-era-for-female-entrepreneurship-activity-7394785371517132800-f79q&trk=public_post_nav-header-join) [](https://www.linkedin.com/login?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww%2Elinkedin%2Ecom%2Fposts%2Funiofyork_building-a-new-era-for-female-entrepreneurship-activity-7394785371517132800-f79q&fromSignIn=true&trk=public_post_nav-header-signin)\n\n# Launch of A New Era for Female Enterprise report in York and North Yorkshire\n\nThis title was summarized by AI from the post below.\n\n [](https://uk.linkedin.com/school/uniofyork/?trk=public_post_feed-actor-image)\n\n[University of York](https://uk.linkedin.com/school/uniofyork/?trk=public_post_feed-actor-name)\n\n178,477 followers\n\n4mo\n\n*   [Report this post](https://www.linkedin.com/uas/login?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fposts%2Funiofyork_building-a-new-era-for-female-entrepreneurship-activity-7394785371517132800-f79q&trk=public_post_ellipsis-menu-semaphore-sign-in-redirect&guestReportContentType=POST&_f=guest-reporting)\n\nA huge thank you to everyone who joined us for the launch of the A New Era for Female Enterprise research last month 👏 The findings of the report were clear: the UK is failing female-led businesses. Despite more than three-quarters of respondents having ambitions to grow or scale up their businesses, not a single government contract was awarded to a female-led business in York and North Yorkshire in the last 12 months. [Enterprise Works at the University of York](https://uk.linkedin.com/showcase/enterprise-works-at-the-university-of-york/?trk=public_post-text) is here to change that. Find out how we're driving change in our region: [https://lnkd.in/eScHDxcU](https://www.linkedin.com/redir/redirect?url=https%3A%2F%2Flnkd%2Ein%2FeScHDxcU&urlhash=v26s&trk=public_post-text) [#UniOfYork](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fhashtag%2Funiofyork&trk=public_post-text) [#UniversityOfYork](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fhashtag%2Funiversityofyork&trk=public_post-text) [#YorkshireBusiness](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fhashtag%2Fyorkshirebusiness&trk=public_post-text)\n\n [](https://uk.linkedin.com/showcase/enterprise-works-at-the-university-of-york/?trk=public_post_reshare_feed-actor-image)\n\n[Enterprise Works at the University of York](https://uk.linkedin.com/showcase/enterprise-works-at-the-university-of-york/?trk=public_post_reshare_feed-actor-name)\n\n1,605 followers\n\n4mo\n\n𝐁𝐮𝐢𝐥𝐝𝐢𝐧𝐠 𝐚 𝐭𝐡𝐫𝐢𝐯𝐢𝐧𝐠 𝐟𝐮𝐭𝐮𝐫𝐞 𝐟𝐨𝐫 𝐘𝐨𝐫𝐤 𝐚𝐧𝐝 𝐍𝐨𝐫𝐭𝐡 𝐘𝐨𝐫𝐤𝐬𝐡𝐢𝐫𝐞’𝐬 𝐟𝐞𝐦𝐚𝐥𝐞 𝐞𝐧𝐭𝐫𝐞𝐩𝐫𝐞𝐧𝐞𝐮𝐫𝐬 A few weeks ago, we brought together entrepreneurs, policymakers, and business leaders for the From Insight to Impact event - a pivotal step in advancing inclusive enterprise across York and North Yorkshire. The research we launched, A New Era for Female Enterprise, revealed both the barriers and the enormous opportunity that lie in backing women-led businesses. Unlocking this potential could add £2.6 billion in GVA and create 165,000 jobs for our region - and that’s before we even begin to measure the social impact this transformation will have on our communities, families, and future generations. The findings were stark: ➡️Female-led businesses raised just £62,000 in equity last year, compared to £3.8 million for male-led ventures. ➡️Not a single pound of government contracts went to female-led firms — while £27.2 million went to male-led businesses. ➡️There are 23,562 fewer self-employed women than men in York and North Yorkshire, with men nearly twice as likely to be self-employed. These figures highlight more than a funding gap - they reveal a system in need of bold, collaborative change. At Enterprise Works, we’re proud to be driving that change. Working alongside partners including the [University of York](https://uk.linkedin.com/school/uniofyork/?trk=public_post_reshare-text), the [York & North Yorkshire Growth Hub](https://uk.linkedin.com/company/ynygrowthhub?trk=public_post_reshare-text), [NatWest Group](https://uk.linkedin.com/company/natwest-group?trk=public_post_reshare-text), and [Federation of Small Businesses (FSB)](https://uk.linkedin.com/company/federation-of-small-businesses?trk=public_post_reshare-text), we’re: ➡️Expanding dedicated programmes that equip female entrepreneurs to start and scale. ➡️Strengthening investment pathways and addressing bias in access to finance. ➡️Championing allyship and visibility, ensuring women are heard, valued, and supported at every stage of business growth. And this is just the beginning. In the coming weeks, we’ll be unveiling a 10-point plan for female enterprise - a practical blueprint to inform policy, accelerate change, and make York and North Yorkshire the UK’s most inclusive region for entrepreneurship. We’re not here to make the system fairer at the edges - we’re here to reimagine it. Huge thank you to our speakers from the event [Rita Collins](https://uk.linkedin.com/in/rita-collins-131266167?trk=public_post_reshare-text) - Natwest, [Lyndsay Mitcheson](https://uk.linkedin.com/in/lyndsay-mitcheson-a146b97a?trk=public_post_reshare-text) - NeoWalk, Jennifer Wood - [York and North Yorkshire Combined Authority](https://uk.linkedin.com/company/ynyca?trk=public_post_reshare-text), [Helen Oldham](https://uk.linkedin.com/in/helen-oldham-46aa8324?trk=public_post_reshare-text) - Lifted Ventures, [Claire Douglas](https://uk.linkedin.com/in/claire-douglas-3434385?trk=public_post_reshare-text) - CYC, [Harriet L Stainton](https://uk.linkedin.com/in/harrietstainton?trk=public_post_reshare-text) - Y&NY Growth Hub [https://lnkd.in/eEfiS7NS](https://lnkd.in/eEfiS7NS?trk=public_post_reshare-text) [#FemaleFounders](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fhashtag%2Ffemalefounders&trk=public_post_reshare-text) [#InclusiveEnterprise](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fhashtag%2Finclusiveenterprise&trk=public_post_reshare-text) [#YorkshireBusiness](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fhashtag%2Fyorkshirebusiness&trk=public_post_reshare-text)\n\n[\n\n### Building a New Era for Female Entrepreneurship in York and North Yorkshire\n\n](https://www.linkedin.com/redir/redirect?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww%2Eyoutube%2Ecom%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DZvRkKNzge9Y&urlhash=6TmU&trk=public_post_reshare_ingested-content-summary-external-video-content)\n\n#### https://www.youtube.com/\n\n [5](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww%2Elinkedin%2Ecom%2Fposts%2Funiofyork_building-a-new-era-for-female-entrepreneurship-activity-7394785371517132800-f79q&trk=public_post_social-actions-reactions)\n\n[Like](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww%2Elinkedin%2Ecom%2Fposts%2Funiofyork_building-a-new-era-for-female-entrepreneurship-activity-7394785371517132800-f79q&trk=public_post_like-cta) [Comment](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww%2Elinkedin%2Ecom%2Fposts%2Funiofyork_building-a-new-era-for-female-entrepreneurship-activity-7394785371517132800-f79q&trk=public_post_comment-cta)\n\nShare\n\n*   Copy\n*   LinkedIn\n*   Facebook\n*   X\n\nTo view or add a comment, [sign in](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww%2Elinkedin%2Ecom%2Fposts%2Funiofyork_building-a-new-era-for-female-entrepreneurship-activity-7394785371517132800-f79q&trk=public_post_feed-cta-banner-cta)\n\n## More Relevant Posts\n\n*   [](https://www.linkedin.com/posts/enterprise-works-at-the-university-of-york_building-a-new-era-for-female-entrepreneurship-activity-7394719022061154304-1GTO)\n    \n     [](https://uk.linkedin.com/showcase/enterprise-works-at-the-university-of-york/?trk=public_post_feed-actor-image)\n    \n    [Enterprise Works at the University of York](https://uk.linkedin.com/showcase/enterprise-works-at-the-university-of-york/?trk=public_post_feed-actor-name)\n    \n    1,605 followers\n    \n    4mo\n    \n    *   [Report this post](https://www.linkedin.com/uas/login?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fposts%2Fenterprise-works-at-the-university-of-york_building-a-new-era-for-female-entrepreneurship-activity-7394719022061154304-1GTO&trk=public_post_ellipsis-menu-semaphore-sign-in-redirect&guestReportContentType=POST&_f=guest-reporting)\n    \n    𝐁𝐮𝐢𝐥𝐝𝐢𝐧𝐠 𝐚 𝐭𝐡𝐫𝐢𝐯𝐢𝐧𝐠 𝐟𝐮𝐭𝐮𝐫𝐞 𝐟𝐨𝐫 𝐘𝐨𝐫𝐤 𝐚𝐧𝐝 𝐍𝐨𝐫𝐭𝐡 𝐘𝐨𝐫𝐤𝐬𝐡𝐢𝐫𝐞’𝐬 𝐟𝐞𝐦𝐚𝐥𝐞 𝐞𝐧𝐭𝐫𝐞𝐩𝐫𝐞𝐧𝐞𝐮𝐫𝐬 A few weeks ago, we brought together entrepreneurs, policymakers, and business leaders for the From Insight to Impact event - a pivotal step in advancing inclusive enterprise across York and North Yorkshire. The research we launched, A New Era for Female Enterprise, revealed both the barriers and the enormous opportunity that lie in backing women-led businesses. Unlocking this potential could add £2.6 billion in GVA and create 165,000 jobs for our region - and that’s before we even begin to measure the social impact this transformation will have on our communities, families, and future generations. The findings were stark: ➡️Female-led businesses raised just £62,000 in equity last year, compared to £3.8 million for male-led ventures. ➡️Not a single pound of government contracts went to female-led firms — while £27.2 million went to male-led businesses. ➡️There are 23,562 fewer self-employed women than men in York and North Yorkshire, with men nearly twice as likely to be self-employed. These figures highlight more than a funding gap - they reveal a system in need of bold, collaborative change. At Enterprise Works, we’re proud to be driving that change. Working alongside partners including the [University of York](https://uk.linkedin.com/school/uniofyork/?trk=public_post-text), the [York & North Yorkshire Growth Hub](https://uk.linkedin.com/company/ynygrowthhub?trk=public_post-text), [NatWest Group](https://uk.linkedin.com/company/natwest-group?trk=public_post-text), and [Federation of Small Businesses (FSB)](https://uk.linkedin.com/company/federation-of-small-businesses?trk=public_post-text), we’re: ➡️Expanding dedicated programmes that equip female entrepreneurs to start and scale. ➡️Strengthening investment pathways and addressing bias in access to finance. ➡️Championing allyship and visibility, ensuring women are heard, valued, and supported at every stage of business growth. And this is just the beginning. In the coming weeks, we’ll be unveiling a 10-point plan for female enterprise - a practical blueprint to inform policy, accelerate change, and make York and North Yorkshire the UK’s most inclusive region for entrepreneurship. We’re not here to make the system fairer at the edges - we’re here to reimagine it. Huge thank you to our speakers from the event [Rita Collins](https://uk.linkedin.com/in/rita-collins-131266167?trk=public_post-text) - Natwest, [Lyndsay Mitcheson](https://uk.linkedin.com/in/lyndsay-mitcheson-a146b97a?trk=public_post-text) - NeoWalk, Jennifer Wood - [York and North Yorkshire Combined Authority](https://uk.linkedin.com/company/ynyca?trk=public_post-text), [Helen Oldham](https://uk.linkedin.com/in/helen-oldham-46aa8324?trk=public_post-text) - Lifted Ventures, [Claire Douglas](https://uk.linkedin.com/in/claire-douglas-3434385?trk=public_post-text) - CYC, [Harriet L Stainton](https://uk.linkedin.com/in/harrietstainton?trk=public_post-text) - Y&NY Growth Hub [https://lnkd.in/eEfiS7NS](https://www.linkedin.com/redir/redirect?url=https%3A%2F%2Flnkd%2Ein%2FeEfiS7NS&urlhash=LRig&trk=public_post-text) [#FemaleFounders](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fhashtag%2Ffemalefounders&trk=public_post-text) [#InclusiveEnterprise](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fhashtag%2Finclusiveenterprise&trk=public_post-text) [#YorkshireBusiness](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fhashtag%2Fyorkshirebusiness&trk=public_post-text)\n    \n    …more\n    \n    [\n    \n    ### Building a New Era for Female Entrepreneurship in York and North Yorkshire\n    \n    ](https://www.linkedin.com/redir/redirect?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww%2Eyoutube%2Ecom%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DZvRkKNzge9Y&urlhash=6TmU&trk=public_post_ingested-content-summary-external-video-content)\n    \n    #### https://www.youtube.com/\n    \n       [18](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fposts%2Fenterprise-works-at-the-university-of-york_building-a-new-era-for-female-entrepreneurship-activity-7394719022061154304-1GTO&trk=public_post_social-actions-reactions) [1 Comment](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fposts%2Fenterprise-works-at-the-university-of-york_building-a-new-era-for-female-entrepreneurship-activity-7394719022061154304-1GTO&trk=public_post_social-actions-comments)\n    \n    [Like](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fposts%2Fenterprise-works-at-the-university-of-york_building-a-new-era-for-female-entrepreneurship-activity-7394719022061154304-1GTO&trk=public_post_like-cta) [Comment](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fposts%2Fenterprise-works-at-the-university-of-york_building-a-new-era-for-female-entrepreneurship-activity-7394719022061154304-1GTO&trk=public_post_comment-cta)\n    \n    Share\n    \n    *   Copy\n    *   LinkedIn\n    *   Facebook\n    *   X\n    \n    To view or add a comment, [sign in](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fposts%2Fenterprise-works-at-the-university-of-york_building-a-new-era-for-female-entrepreneurship-activity-7394719022061154304-1GTO&trk=public_post_feed-cta-banner-cta)\n    \n*   [](https://www.linkedin.com/posts/kiran-trehan-48a8086_building-a-new-era-for-female-entrepreneurship-activity-7394705719129944064-uPJX)\n    \n     [](https://uk.linkedin.com/in/kiran-trehan-48a8086?trk=public_post_feed-actor-image)\n    \n    [Kiran Trehan](https://uk.linkedin.com/in/kiran-trehan-48a8086?trk=public_post_feed-actor-name)\n    \n    4mo\n    \n    *   [Report this post](https://www.linkedin.com/uas/login?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fposts%2Fkiran-trehan-48a8086_building-a-new-era-for-female-entrepreneurship-activity-7394705719129944064-uPJX&trk=public_post_ellipsis-menu-semaphore-sign-in-redirect&guestReportContentType=POST&_f=guest-reporting)\n    \n    ✨ Building a thriving future for York and North Yorkshire’s female entrepreneurs ✨ A few weeks ago, I had the privilege of joining an extraordinary group of entrepreneurs, policymakers, and regional partners for the 'From Insight to Impact' event — a pivotal step in shaping the future of inclusive enterprise in York and North Yorkshire. The message was clear: 🔓 unlocking the potential of women-led businesses is one of the biggest economic opportunities of our time - supporting female founders to start and scale, York and North Yorkshire could generate £2.6 billion in additional GVA and create 165,000 new jobs. But beyond the economic potential lies something even more powerful; the social impact of inclusive enterprise. When women start and scale businesses, they reinvest in their communities, create flexible, fair employment, and inspire the next generation of entrepreneurs. 📊 Yet the research data spells out so clearly that we still have structural barriers to dismantle: 💡 Female-led businesses raised just £62,000 in equity last year, compared with £3.8 million for male-led ventures. 💡 Not a single pound of government contracts went to female-led firms - while £27.2 million went to male-led businesses. 💡 There are 23,562 fewer self-employed women than men, with men nearly twice as likely to be self-employed. This isn’t just a fairness issue - it’s an economic inefficiency. Every barrier that holds back women in enterprise holds back our region’s productivity, resilience, and innovation. At the [University of York](https://uk.linkedin.com/school/uniofyork/?trk=public_post-text), through [Enterprise Works at the University of York](https://uk.linkedin.com/showcase/enterprise-works-at-the-university-of-york/?trk=public_post-text), we are working with partners across the public, private, and education sectors to make inclusion a foundation of our regional economic strategy by: 🌟 Embedding inclusive enterprise into our devolution and economic strategies - ensuring all communities can participate in growth. 🌟 Reforming investment and procurement systems to make access to capital and contracts fairer and more transparent. 🌟 Strengthening mentorship, allyship, and leadership networks, recognising that visible success changes expectations for what’s possible.  In the coming weeks, we will be revealing a 10-point plan for female enterprise; a blueprint for action that will help shape future policy and practice across our region, transforming how our economy values, funds, and grows enterprise, so that every entrepreneur, from every community, can contribute to regional prosperity. With special thanks to: [🌟Andrea Morrison🌟](https://uk.linkedin.com/in/%F0%9F%8C%9Fandrea-morrison%F0%9F%8C%9F-80295031?trk=public_post-text) (FSB), [Lyndsay Mitcheson](https://uk.linkedin.com/in/lyndsay-mitcheson-a146b97a?trk=public_post-text), [Claire Douglas](https://uk.linkedin.com/in/claire-douglas-3434385?trk=public_post-text), [Helen Oldham](https://uk.linkedin.com/in/helen-oldham-46aa8324?trk=public_post-text), [Rita Collins](https://uk.linkedin.com/in/rita-collins-131266167?trk=public_post-text), [Harriet L Stainton](https://uk.linkedin.com/in/harrietstainton?trk=public_post-text), Jennifer Wood, as well as [Federation of Small Businesses (FSB)](https://uk.linkedin.com/company/federation-of-small-businesses?trk=public_post-text), [York and North Yorkshire Combined Authority](https://uk.linkedin.com/company/ynyca?trk=public_post-text), and [City of York Council](https://uk.linkedin.com/company/cityofyork?trk=public_post-text), [#FemaleFounders](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fhashtag%2Ffemalefounders&trk=public_post-text) [#InclusiveEntrepreneurship](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fhashtag%2Finclusiveentrepreneurship&trk=public_post-text) [#WomenInBusiness](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fhashtag%2Fwomeninbusiness&trk=public_post-text) [#YorkshireBusiness](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fhashtag%2Fyorkshirebusiness&trk=public_post-text) [#YorkshireEnterprise](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fhashtag%2Fyorkshireenterprise&trk=public_post-text) [#FemaleEntrepreneurship](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fhashtag%2Ffemaleentrepreneurship&trk=public_post-text) [#RegionalGrowth](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fhashtag%2Fregionalgrowth&trk=public_post-text)   [https://lnkd.in/eaXBVdxA](https://www.linkedin.com/redir/redirect?url=https%3A%2F%2Flnkd%2Ein%2FeaXBVdxA&urlhash=oIaO&trk=public_post-text)\n    \n    …more\n    \n    [\n    \n    ### Building a New Era for Female Entrepreneurship in York and North Yorkshire\n    \n    ](https://www.linkedin.com/redir/redirect?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww%2Eyoutube%2Ecom%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DZvRkKNzge9Y&urlhash=6TmU&trk=public_post_ingested-content-summary-external-video-content)\n    \n    #### https://www.youtube.com/\n    \n       [90](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fposts%2Fkiran-trehan-48a8086_building-a-new-era-for-female-entrepreneurship-activity-7394705719129944064-uPJX&trk=public_post_social-actions-reactions) [11 Comments](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fposts%2Fkiran-trehan-48a8086_building-a-new-era-for-female-entrepreneurship-activity-7394705719129944064-uPJX&trk=public_post_social-actions-comments)\n    \n    [Like](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fposts%2Fkiran-trehan-48a8086_building-a-new-era-for-female-entrepreneurship-activity-7394705719129944064-uPJX&trk=public_post_like-cta) [Comment](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fposts%2Fkiran-trehan-48a8086_building-a-new-era-for-female-entrepreneurship-activity-7394705719129944064-uPJX&trk=public_post_comment-cta)\n    \n    Share\n    \n    *   Copy\n    *   LinkedIn\n    *   Facebook\n    *   X\n    \n    To view or add a comment, [sign in](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fposts%2Fkiran-trehan-48a8086_building-a-new-era-for-female-entrepreneurship-activity-7394705719129944064-uPJX&trk=public_post_feed-cta-banner-cta)\n    \n*   [](https://www.linkedin.com/posts/katherine-walker-sherpas_the-rise-report-of-female-entrepreneurship-activity-7385963709460041728-DxWG)\n    \n     [](https://uk.linkedin.com/in/katherine-walker-sherpas?trk=public_post_feed-actor-image)\n    \n    [Katherine Walker](https://uk.linkedin.com/in/katherine-walker-sherpas?trk=public_post_feed-actor-name)\n    \n    5mo Edited\n    \n    *   [Report this post](https://www.linkedin.com/uas/login?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fposts%2Fkatherine-walker-sherpas_the-rise-report-of-female-entrepreneurship-activity-7385963709460041728-DxWG&trk=public_post_ellipsis-menu-semaphore-sign-in-redirect&guestReportContentType=POST&_f=guest-reporting)\n    \n    🔊 Are we truly listening to female entrepreneurs? In York and North Yorkshire, steps are being taken to ensure women’s voices are included - the [University of York](https://uk.linkedin.com/school/uniofyork/?trk=public_post-text)'s recent New Era for Female Entrepreneurship report (link in messages) is a significant move in the right direction. It gives us a much-needed view into the current state of play for female-led businesses across the region. But the data is stark: 📉 £0 in government contracts awarded to female-led businesses in the last 12 months 📉 £62k in equity raised by female-led organisations, compared to £3.8m by male-led and £1.8m by mixed-gender teams 📉 Only 7 female-led businesses in the region are involved in import/export (vs 199 male-led) And it’s not just about funding or visibility. It’s about designing systems that actually reflect the lives women are living. 57% of women surveyed in the report said that the mental load of balancing business with everyday life is a barrier to growth and continuity. And here’s where it gets personal. In North Yorkshire, a recent change to the school transport policy means hundreds of families are now required to drive their children to school. In my case, because we live just 300 metres closer to a school in York, we’re no longer eligible for transport to our actual catchment school in Tadcaster, even though both schools are over six miles away. For now, we’re paying £818 a year for a bus pass, but the long-term intention is to remove services wherever possible. In many parts of North Yorkshire, that’s already happened. If that happens, it would mean a 50-minute round trip, twice a day - costing up to 10 hours a week that I could otherwise spend building a business. Because let’s be honest - that burden will fall, predictably and disproportionately, on women. We know this because 77% of the 898 members of the School Action Transport Group in North Yorkshire are women. They are not just the female workforce and business owners, they are also carers and parents. And right now, they are fighting not just for their children, but for their ability to stay in work. 🚨 Unless we start thinking about entrepreneurship in the whole, we risk designing and passing policies that actively make it harder for women to succeed. That’s why this has become my personal mission: to ensure a robust impact assessment is introduced to policy change across education, transport, and care - one that fully evaluates the effects on the female workforce of any policy change. And the first step is better data. That’s why the team at [Female Founders Rise](https://uk.linkedin.com/company/female-founders-rise?trk=public_post-text) is gathering insight via The Rise Report - and your voice matters. 💥 Please take 10 minutes to complete the survey: 👉 [https://lnkd.in/eFSA5g3b](https://www.linkedin.com/redir/redirect?url=https%3A%2F%2Flnkd%2Ein%2FeFSA5g3b&urlhash=lf7I&trk=public_post-text) Because good data leads to better decisions. [#socialvalue](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fhashtag%2Fsocialvalue&trk=public_post-text) [#innovation](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fhashtag%2Finnovation&trk=public_post-text) [#FemaleEntrepreneurs](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fhashtag%2Ffemaleentrepreneurs&trk=public_post-text) [#InclusivePolicy](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fhashtag%2Finclusivepolicy&trk=public_post-text) [#RiseReport](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fhashtag%2Frisereport&trk=public_post-text) [#WomenInBusiness](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fhashtag%2Fwomeninbusiness&trk=public_post-text)\n    \n    [\n    \n    The Rise Report of Female Entrepreneurship therisereport.co.uk\n    \n    \n    \n    ](https://www.linkedin.com/redir/redirect?url=https%3A%2F%2Ftherisereport%2Eco%2Euk%2F&urlhash=5Agp&trk=public_post_feed-article-content)\n    \n       [15](