rtContentType=POST&_f=guest-reporting)\n    \n    [#VentureForward](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fhashtag%2Fventureforward&trk=public_post-text) Workshop 5 – COMPLETED ✅ This week, Lizzie F. Founder of [PWR Women](https://www.linkedin.com/company/pwr-women?trk=public_post-text) shared her reflections on our latest session, where we dived into the realities of building a business straight from the voices of early-stage founders in our portfolio. Our cohort were introduced to two of our best female founders - [Laura Pomfret (Financielle) 💸](https://uk.linkedin.com/in/laurapomfret?trk=public_post-text)and [Bella Trang Ngo](https://uk.linkedin.com/in/bellango?trk=public_post-text) from [Brarista](https://uk.linkedin.com/company/brarista?trk=public_post-text).   They spoke candidly about their journeys after their successful pre-seed raises, covering the lessons learned, the unexpected challenges, and the difference between pitching an idea and actually scaling a business 😬 Their stories were a powerful reminder that with passion, belief in your vision, and resilience, success is possible 🙌 [#VentureForward](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fhashtag%2Fventureforward&trk=public_post-text) [#Founders](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fhashtag%2Ffounders&trk=public_post-text) [#InvestmentReadiness](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fhashtag%2Finvestmentreadiness&trk=public_post-text) [#InvestorMindset](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fhashtag%2Finvestormindset&trk=public_post-text) [#Entrepreneurship](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fhashtag%2Fentrepreneurship&trk=public_post-text) [#BusinessResilience](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fhashtag%2Fbusinessresilience&trk=public_post-text) [#GreaterManchester](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fhashtag%2Fgreatermanchester&trk=public_post-text) [#InnovationNorth](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fhashtag%2Finnovationnorth&trk=public_post-text) [Ranvir Singh MBA, LLM, MA(Oxon)](https://uk.linkedin.com/in/ranvir-singh-mba-llm-ma-oxon-93786116b?trk=public_post-text) [Marc Shirman](https://uk.linkedin.com/in/marc-shirman-aab1039?trk=public_post-text) [Mountside Ventures](https://uk.linkedin.com/company/mountsideventures?trk=public_post-text) [Stronger Stories](https://uk.linkedin.com/company/stronger-stories?trk=public_post-text) [Firstport](https://uk.linkedin.com/company/firstport?trk=public_post-text) [Foundervine](https://uk.linkedin.com/company/foundervine?trk=public_post-text) [Innovate UK](https://uk.linkedin.com/company/innovateuk?trk=public_post-text)\n    \n    …more\n    \n       [38](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fposts%2Fgc-angels_ventureforward-ventureforward-founders-activity-7391900391397027840-pPG3&trk=public_post_social-actions-reactions) [1 Comment](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fposts%2Fgc-angels_ventureforward-ventureforward-founders-activity-7391900391397027840-pPG3&trk=public_post_social-actions-comments)\n    \n    [Like](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fposts%2Fgc-angels_ventureforward-ventureforward-founders-activity-7391900391397027840-pPG3&trk=public_post_like-cta) [Comment](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fposts%2Fgc-angels_ventureforward-ventureforward-founders-activity-7391900391397027840-pPG3&trk=public_post_comment-cta)\n    \n    Share\n    \n    *   Copy\n    *   LinkedIn\n    *   Facebook\n    *   X\n    \n    To view or add a comment, [sign in](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fposts%2Fgc-angels_ventureforward-ventureforward-founders-activity-7391900391397027840-pPG3&trk=public_post_feed-cta-banner-cta)\n    \n*   [](https://www.linkedin.com/posts/midlands-business-journal_building-beyond-barriers-how-nebraska-women-activity-7394705659922948096-og4s)\n    \n     [](https://www.linkedin.com/company/midlands-business-journal?trk=public_post_feed-actor-image)\n    \n    [Midlands Business Journal](https://www.linkedin.com/company/midlands-business-journal?trk=public_post_feed-actor-name)\n    \n    3,270 followers\n    \n    4mo\n    \n    *   [Report this post](https://www.linkedin.com/uas/login?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fposts%2Fmidlands-business-journal_building-beyond-barriers-how-nebraska-women-activity-7394705659922948096-og4s&trk=public_post_ellipsis-menu-semaphore-sign-in-redirect&guestReportContentType=POST&_f=guest-reporting)\n    \n    Building Beyond Barriers: How Nebraska Women Entrepreneurs Are Redefining Leadership For many women entrepreneurs, the path to leadership isn't a straight line—it's a series of pivots, leaps of faith, and moments of rediscovery. In Nebraska, that journey is unfolding with remarkable resilience and creativity. Erica Wassinger, founding partner at Proven Ventures and longtime advocate for Nebraska startups, says one of the biggest myths holding women back is the belief that starting a business requires total sacrifice. \"When you strip it down, starting a company really comes down to two things: knowing a problem your customer has and talking to potential customers about it,\" Wassinger says. The misconception that every piece must be perfect before you start echoes across many women founders' experiences. Karine Sokpoh's journey exemplifies this adaptive approach. Born and raised in Togo, she immigrated to the United States and eventually settled in Omaha, where she built 402 Legal and founded the Midlands African Chamber. Starting with just nine members in December 2020—in the middle of the pandemic—the chamber has grown to more than 290 members in just five years. \"As an immigrant, especially from a non-English-speaking country, you lose so much of your identity at first,\" Sokpoh reflects. \"But that experience taught me adaptability, resilience, and deep gratitude. It also revealed how many systems weren't built with people like you in mind.\" She doesn't mince words about the barriers: \"Black and brown women entrepreneurs are often undercapitalized, underestimated, and over-mentored. We need to be trusted more and given the same grace to make mistakes that others are afforded.\" Chloe Tran-Thompson, owner of The Bánh Mì Shop, emphasizes that timing matters as much as planning. \"I think the biggest myth is that it's this big, daunting thing and you need to have everything figured out when you start. The reality is you can choose to start as small as suits you and figure it out as you go.\" These Nebraska entrepreneurs are proving that leadership looks different for everyone—and that's exactly the point. Read the complete Women's Entrepreneurship Day feature in this week's MBJ. [#WomensEntrepreneurshipDay](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fhashtag%2Fwomensentrepreneurshipday&trk=public_post-text) [#NebraskaWomen](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fhashtag%2Fnebraskawomen&trk=public_post-text) [#Leadership](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fhashtag%2Fleadership&trk=public_post-text) [#Entrepreneurship](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fhashtag%2Fentrepreneurship&trk=public_post-text) [#DiversityInBusiness](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fhashtag%2Fdiversityinbusiness&trk=public_post-text) [https://lnkd.in/gsRkrcuq](https://www.linkedin.com/redir/redirect?url=https%3A%2F%2Flnkd%2Ein%2FgsRkrcuq&urlhash=zCHV&trk=public_post-text)\n    \n    [\n    \n    Building Beyond Barriers: How Nebraska Women Entrepreneurs are Redefining Leadership mbj.com\n    \n    \n    \n    ](https://www.linkedin.com/redir/redirect?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww%2Embj%2Ecom%2Ffeatured%2Fbuilding-beyond-barriers-how-nebraska-women-entrepreneurs-are-redefining-leadership%2Farticle_43f3f020-ec0f-407b-8d42-2c751e3fa0e1%2Ehtml&urlhash=k0Ai&trk=public_post_feed-article-content)\n    \n    [Like](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fposts%2Fmidlands-business-journal_building-beyond-barriers-how-nebraska-women-activity-7394705659922948096-og4s&trk=public_post_like-cta) [Comment](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fposts%2Fmidlands-business-journal_building-beyond-barriers-how-nebraska-women-activity-7394705659922948096-og4s&trk=public_post_comment-cta)\n    \n    Share\n    \n    *   Copy\n    *   LinkedIn\n    *   Facebook\n    *   X\n    \n    To view or add a comment, [sign in](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fposts%2Fmidlands-business-journal_building-beyond-barriers-how-nebraska-women-activity-7394705659922948096-og4s&trk=public_post_feed-cta-banner-cta)\n    \n*   [](https://www.linkedin.com/posts/pronoia-communications_a-womens-entrepreneurial-summit-small-business-activity-7386789730975334400-MCmT)\n    \n     [](https://ca.linkedin.com/company/pronoia-communications?trk=public_post_feed-actor-image)\n    \n    [Pronoia Communications](https://ca.linkedin.com/company/pronoia-communications?trk=public_post_feed-actor-name)\n    \n    2 followers\n    \n    5mo\n    \n    *   [Report this post](https://www.linkedin.com/uas/login?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fposts%2Fpronoia-communications_a-womens-entrepreneurial-summit-small-business-activity-7386789730975334400-MCmT&trk=public_post_ellipsis-menu-semaphore-sign-in-redirect&guestReportContentType=POST&_f=guest-reporting)\n    \n    It's [#SmallBusinessWeek](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fhashtag%2Fsmallbusinessweek&trk=public_post-text) in Canada and let's want to talk about the entrepreneurial journey of women. Only 4% of venture capital funding in Canada goes to women-led businesses. Let that sink in. Women entrepreneurs are making incredible strides, but access to capital remains a barrier to growth. On the positive side, the Government of Canada’s Women Entrepreneurship Strategy (WES) has invested nearly $2 billion to support women entrepreneurs through financing, networks, and expertise. And in some areas, women-majority businesses are leading the way — about 6% of women-owned SMEs accessed government loans or grants, compared to 3.2% of men-owned firms. Add to that the incredible organizations driving change — like [WeBC](https://ca.linkedin.com/company/thewebc?trk=public_post-text), the [Women Entrepreneurship Knowledge Hub (WEKH)](https://ca.linkedin.com/company/wekh-pcfe?trk=public_post-text), and [Startup Canada](https://ca.linkedin.com/company/startup-canada?trk=public_post-text)’s Women program, who are creating ecosystems of mentorship, funding, and knowledge that help women entrepreneurs not just start, but thrive. At [Pronoia Communications](https://ca.linkedin.com/company/pronoia-communications?trk=public_post-text), it is our dream to play a part in that ecosystem as a purpose-driven brand strategy and storytelling consultancy empowering women entrepreneurs to define their why and step into their purpose, bring their brand story to life, and build businesses that matter beyond profit. That is why Pronoia is excited an the opportunity to be a vendor at the @YWCA Women’s Entrepreneurial Summit this Small Business Week, joining an inspiring community of women who are redefining success, supporting one another, and proving that business can be both profitable and purposeful. Let’s bridge that 4% gap — not just with funding —but with powerful, purpose-led stories that make people believe in what we’re building. [#WomenEntrepreneurs](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fhashtag%2Fwomenentrepreneurs&trk=public_post-text) [#PurposeDrivenBusiness](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fhashtag%2Fpurposedrivenbusiness&trk=public_post-text) [#SmallBusinessWeek](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fhashtag%2Fsmallbusinessweek&trk=public_post-text) [#YWCA](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fhashtag%2Fywca&trk=public_post-text) [#WomenInBusiness](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fhashtag%2Fwomeninbusiness&trk=public_post-text) [#BrandStrategy](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fhashtag%2Fbrandstrategy&trk=public_post-text) [#Storytelling](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fhashtag%2Fstorytelling&trk=public_post-text) [#PronoiaCommunications](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fhashtag%2Fpronoiacommunications&trk=public_post-text) [#WeBC](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fhashtag