      "description": "Aug 11, 2025 — While York and North Yorkshire show strong business survival rates, West Yorkshire struggles with productivity, skills gaps, and persistent ...Read more",
      "relevance_score": 0.60546875,
      "content": "     Does the Yorkshire economy need help? - The Yorkshire Society                                                                [Skip to content](#content)\n\n[![](https://theyorkshiresociety.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/YS_Main-Logo_Colour.png)](https://theyorkshiresociety.org/)\n\n[](#awb-open-oc__97)\n\n## Does the Yorkshire economy need help?\n\nAugust 11, 2025|[Uncategorized](https://theyorkshiresociety.org/category/uncategorized/)| [0 comments on Does the Yorkshire economy need help?](https://theyorkshiresociety.org/does-the-yorkshire-economy-need-help/#respond)|\n\n![](https://theyorkshiresociety.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/Drax.jpg \"Drax\")\n\n### We asked AI “Does the Yorkshire economy need help” and were not surprised with the answer…\n\n‘Yes’, the Yorkshire economy, particularly West Yorkshire, faces significant challenges and could benefit from targeted interventions. While York and North Yorkshire show strong business survival rates, West Yorkshire struggles with productivity, skills gaps, and persistent inequalities.\n\nThese issues hinder economic growth and impact living standards across the region. Here’s a more detailed look at West Yorkshire in particular:\n\n*   **Low Productivity:**\n\nWest Yorkshire’s productivity growth has not kept pace with the rest of the UK, and projections suggest this gap will widen in the coming years.\n\n*   **Skills Gap:**\n\nA significant portion of the workforce lacks the necessary skills and qualifications to fully participate in the economy, which limits their potential and hinders overall productivity.\n\n*   **Persistent Inequalities:**\n\nDisadvantaged groups, including women, ethnic minorities, disabled people, and older people, face barriers to employment and economic advancement.\n\n*   **Economic Inactivity:**\n\nHigh levels of economic inactivity and health inequalities further contribute to the region’s economic challenges.\n\nWhat are the impacts of these issues in the real world?\n\n*   **Lower Living Standards:**\n\nThe productivity gap translates into lower wages and living standards for many residents.\n\n*   **Widening Inequality:**\n\nEntrenched inequalities, including relative poverty and ill health, are exacerbated by the region’s economic struggles.\n\n*   **Missed Economic Potential:**\n\nClosing the productivity gap would unlock significant economic growth, creating more businesses, jobs, and investment opportunities.\n\nPotential Solutions and Initiatives:\n\n*   **Focus on Productivity:**\n\nInvesting in skills development, technological advancements, and innovation to boost productivity across various sectors.\n\n*   **Promote Inclusive Growth:**\n\nTackling inequalities by supporting disadvantaged groups, improving access to employment, and addressing health disparities.\n\n*   **Support Business Growth:**\n\nEncouraging business start-ups, attracting inward investment, and fostering growth in key sectors like green and digital industries.\n\n*   **Infrastructure Development:**\n\nInvesting in digital infrastructure, transport links, and other key infrastructure to support economic activity.\n\n*   **Circular Economy:**\n\nPromoting circular economy practices to enhance resource efficiency, reduce waste, and create new business opportunities.\n\nSeveral initiatives are already underway in West Yorkshire to address these challenges, including the [West Yorkshire Combined Authority’s economic strategy](https://www.westyorks-ca.gov.uk/media/12097/240314-economic-strategy-evidence-pack.pdf) and the Mayor’s £37 million plan to get West Yorkshire working, [according to the West Yorkshire Combined Authority](https://www.westyorks-ca.gov.uk/all-news-and-blogs/mayor-unveils-37-million-plan-to-get-west-yorkshire-working/). These efforts aim to create a more prosperous and equitable future for the region but is it enough?\n\n### What can we do?\n\nWith the greatest respect, £37m at this level is a drop in an ocean.  The Yorkshire Society believes in self-help and encourages Yorkshire (West, North, South and East) to take the initiative, individually and collectively, to improve performance and growth for the greater good as well as the individual businesses on which the greater good ultimately relies.\n\nThe Society’s corporate membership and our approach to it, is designed to provide the kind of support individual businesses need – hands on help dedicated to them specifically.\n\nJOIN THE YORKSHIRE SOCIETY [HERE](https://theyorkshiresociety.org/corporate-membership/)\n\n![](data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns%3D%27http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2F2000%2Fsvg%27%20width%3D%27300%27%20height%3D%27108%27%20viewBox%3D%270%200%20300%20108%27%3E%3Crect%20width%3D%27300%27%20height%3D%27108%27%20fill-opacity%3D%220%22%2F%3E%3C%2Fsvg%3E)\n\n[](https://www.facebook.com/sharer.php?u=https%3A%2F%2Ftheyorkshiresociety.org%2Fdoes-the-yorkshire-economy-need-help%2F&t=Does%20the%20Yorkshire%20economy%20need%20help%3F \"Facebook\")[](https://x.com/intent/post?text=Does%20the%20Yorkshire%20economy%20need%20help%3F&url=https%3A%2F%2Ftheyorkshiresociety.org%2Fdoes-the-yorkshire-economy-need-help%2F \"X\")[](https://www.linkedin.com/shareArticle?mini=true&url=https%3A%2F%2Ftheyorkshiresociety.org%2Fdoes-the-yorkshire-economy-need-help%2F&title=Does%20the%20Yorkshire%20economy%20need%20help%3F&summary=We%20asked%20AI%20%26quot%3BDoes%20the%20Yorkshire%20economy%20need%20help%26quot%3B%20and%20were%20not%20surprised%20with%20the%20answer...%0A%26%2339%3BYes%26%2339%3B%2C%20the%20Yorkshire%20economy%2C%20particularly%20West%20Yorkshire%2C%20faces%20significant%20challenges%20and%20could%20benefit%20from%20targeted%20interventions.%20While%20York%20and%20North%20Yorkshire%20show%20strong%20business%20survival%20rates%2C%20West%20Yorkshire%20struggles%20with%20productivity%2C%20skills%20gaps%2C%20and%20persistent%20inequalities.%0A%0AThese%20issues%20hinder%20economic%20growth \"LinkedIn\")[](https://www.tumblr.com/share/link?url