ta)\n\n## More Relevant Posts\n\n*   [](https://www.linkedin.com/posts/cd-associates-inc-_cdatps-wbe-womenownedbusiness-activity-7383894839614160896-1CKo)\n    \n     [](https://www.linkedin.com/company/cd-associates-inc-?trk=public_post_feed-actor-image)\n    \n    [CD & Associates, Inc.](https://www.linkedin.com/company/cd-associates-inc-?trk=public_post_feed-actor-name)\n    \n    784 followers\n    \n    5mo\n    \n    *   [Report this post](/uas/login?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fposts%2Fcd-associates-inc-_cdatps-wbe-womenownedbusiness-activity-7383894839614160896-1CKo&trk=public_post_ellipsis-menu-semaphore-sign-in-redirect&guestReportContentType=POST&_f=guest-reporting)\n    \n    [Construction Inclusion Week](https://www.linkedin.com/company/construction-inclusion-week?trk=public_post-text) • Day 2: Attract & Retain A thriving construction industry doesn’t just bring people in—it gives them reasons to stay. As demand for skilled team members grows, we have a responsibility to expand how and where we look for talent, while also ensuring those who join our workforce see a clear and meaningful future for themselves. Attracting workers means broadening outreach, opening doors for individuals from all backgrounds, and creating accessible pathways into the industry. Retention comes from the daily experience—work that fosters trust, provides opportunities to grow, and helps every individual find purpose in their role. When organizations commit to both attraction and retention, we build teams that are stronger, more stable, and better prepared for long-term success—together. [#CDAtps](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fhashtag%2Fcdatps&trk=public_post-text) [#WBE](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fhashtag%2Fwbe&trk=public_post-text) [#WomenOwnedBusiness](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%