cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fposts%2Fcd-associates-inc-_cdatps-wbe-womenownedbusiness-activity-7383894839614160896-1CKo&trk=public_post_comment-cta)\n    \n    Share\n    \n    *   Copy\n    *   LinkedIn\n    *   Facebook\n    *   X\n    \n    To view or add a comment, [sign in](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fposts%2Fcd-associates-inc-_cdatps-wbe-womenownedbusiness-activity-7383894839614160896-1CKo&trk=public_post_feed-cta-banner-cta)\n    \n*   [](https://www.linkedin.com/posts/oneworldstrong_lunaawardshouston-anahernandez-laurenashleysimmons-activity-7382844595564441600-Usuc)\n    \n     [](https://www.linkedin.com/in/oneworldstrong?trk=public_post_feed-actor-image)\n    \n    [Jeri Brooks](https://www.linkedin.com/in/oneworldstrong?trk=public_post_feed-actor-name)\n    \n    1K followers\n    \n    5mo Edited\n    \n    *   [Report this post](/uas/login?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fposts%2Foneworldstrong_lunaawardshouston-anahernandez-laurenashleysimmons-activity-7382844595564441600-Usuc&trk=public_post_ellipsis-menu-semaphore-sign-in-redirect&guestReportContentType=POST&_f=guest-reporting)\n    \n    From hard hats to high heels, this year’s [Regional Hispanic Contractors Association (RHCA)](https://www.linkedin.com/company/regional-hispanic-contractors-association-rhca?trk=public_post-text) [#LunaAwardsHouston](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fhashtag%2Flunaawardshouston&trk=public_post-text) proved that when women and minority contractors build, communities rise. Women are the blueprint and shaping the future of construction and community development across Texas. For more than two decades, the RHCA has been breaking barriers, building businesses, and opening doors for women and minority contractors to grow, lead, and thrive. The Luna Awards are their annual reminder that excellence and impact have no ceiling. That spirit of recognition and sisterhood showed up in every part of the program. You know those people in the back making things happen who rarely get the spotlight? We all have that friend- today, I had several honored. Mine are [City of Houston Office of Business Opportunity](https://www.linkedin.com/showcase/houstonobo/?trk=public_post-text) [Cylenthia Hoyrd](https://www.linkedin.com/in/cylenthia-hoyrd-32306a2b?trk=public_post-text) and [Karen Levingston-Franklin. MBA](https://www.linkedin.com/in/karen-levingston-franklin-mba-26309b8?trk=public_post-text), honored as Houston Luna Award Business Advocate of the Year! From [Helen Callier](https://www.linkedin.com/in/helencallier?trk=public_post-text), who set the tone by asking us all to clap for ourselves and declare, “I am a winner,” to the powerful lineup of leaders in the room Chairwoman [#AnaHernandez](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fhashtag%2Fanahernandez&trk=public_post-text), Mayor Pro Tem [Martha Castex-Tatum, MPA](https://www.linkedin.com/in/martha-castex-tatum-mpa-93521a282?trk=public_post-text), State Rep [#LaurenAshleySimmons](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fhashtag%2Flaurenashleysimmons&trk=public_post-text), [#HoustonCityCollege](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fhashtag%2Fhoustoncitycollege&trk=public_post-text) Veronica Davis, Heidi Obie, [Carlecia Wright](https://www.linkedin.com/in/carlecia-wright-437150b?trk=public_post-text) and [City of Houston Mayor's Office](https://www.linkedin.com/company/city-of-houston-mayor-s-office?trk=public_post-text) for People with Disabilities [Angel Ponce](https://www.linkedin.com/in/angel-ponce-trevizo?trk=public_post-text) — every moment reflected what happens when women (and our allies) show up, speak up, and build up one another. But my favorite part? Watching women cheer for women with no hesitation. We’re designing the blueprint, laying the foundation, and leading the build. That kind of energy is what keeps communities rising — because dope women support dope women. Who’s that friend for you? Tag her or add her name in the comments. [#LunaAwardsHouston](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fhashtag%2Flunaawardshouston&trk=public_post-text) [#WomenWhoBuild](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fhashtag%2Fwomenwhobuild&trk=public_post-text) [#PowerPurposePresence](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fhashtag%2Fpowerpurposepresence&trk=public_post-text) [#LeadershipInAction](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fhashtag%2Fleadershipinaction&trk=public_post-text) [#HoustonWomen](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fhashtag%2Fhoustonwomen&trk=public_post-text) [#WeBuildTheTable](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fhashtag%2Fwebuildthetable&trk=public_post-text)\n    \n    …more\n    \n       [45](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fposts%2Foneworldstrong_lunaawardshouston-anahernandez-laurenashleysimmons-activity-7382844595564441600-Usuc&trk=public_post_social-actions-reactions) [3 Comments](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fposts%2Foneworldstrong_lunaawardshouston-anahernandez-laurenashleysimmons-activity-7382844595564441600-Usuc&trk=public_post_social-actions-comments)\n    \n    [Like](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fposts%2Foneworldstrong_lunaawardshouston-anahernandez-laurenashleysimmons-activity-7382844595564441600-Usuc&trk=public_post_like-cta) [Comment](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fposts%2Foneworldstrong_lunaawardshouston-anahernandez-laurenashleysimmons-activity-7382844595564441600-Usuc&trk=public_post_comment-cta)\n    \n    Share\n    \n    *   Copy\n    *   LinkedIn\n    *   Facebook\n    *   X\n    \n    To view or add a comment, [sign in](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fposts%2Foneworldstrong_lunaawardshouston-anahernandez-laurenashleysimmons-activity-7382844595564441600-Usuc&trk=public_post_feed-cta-banner-cta)\n    \n*   [](https://www.linkedin.com/posts/agardner22_constructioninclusionweek-womentalkconstruction-activity-7384692628832821248-qPPp)\n    \n     [](https://www.linkedin.com/in/agardner22?trk=public_post_feed-actor-image)\n    \n    [Angela Gardner](https://www.linkedin.com/in/agardner22?trk=public_post_feed-actor-name)\n    \n    ABC Carolinas Chapter•19K followers\n    \n    5mo\n    \n    *   [Report this post](/uas/login?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fposts%2Fagardner22_constructioninclusionweek-womentalkconstruction-activity-7384692628832821248-qPPp&trk=public_post_ellipsis-menu-semaphore-sign-in-redirect&guestReportContentType=POST&_f=guest-reporting)\n    \n    Celebrating Construction Inclusion Week! 🏗️ This week, we’re celebrating [Construction Inclusion Week](https://www.linkedin.com/company/construction-inclusion-week?trk=public_post-text), a reminder that real strength in our industry comes from diverse voices, inclusive opportunities, and people who care enough to make change happen. At [Women Talk Construction](https://www.linkedin.com/company/women-talk-construction?trk=public_post-text), [Christi Powell](https://www.linkedin.com/in/christi-powell?trk=public_post-text) and I see it every day, especially in our own backyard here in the Carolinas. From [Greenville Technical College](https://www.linkedin.com/school/greenville-technical-college/?trk=public_post-text)’s welding program, where students are learning skills that change lives, to the mentors, educators, and employers building bridges to opportunity, this is inclusion in action. 🚀 Inclusion isn’t just a theme for one week; it’s a movement. 🚀 It’s giving people a place to learn, grow, and lead. 🚀 It’s creating pathways for every person to belong and thrive in construction. To all the women (and men) welding a brighter future, lifting others up, and showing that construction is a place for ALL people; thank you for the difference you make every single day. 🧡 Here’s to the people behind the progress, the educators shaping the next generation, and the communities that prove when we work together, we build better. [#ConstructionInclusionWeek](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fhashtag%2Fconstructioninclusionweek&trk=public_post-text) [#WomenTalkConstruction](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fhashtag%2Fwomentalkconstruction&trk=public_post-text) [#Welding](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fhashtag%2Fwelding&trk=public_post-text) [#BuildingBelonging](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fhashtag%2Fbuildingbelonging&trk=public_post-text) [#TogetherWeBuild](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fhashtag%2Ftogetherwebuild&trk=public_post-text) [Casey Ross](https://www.linkedin.com/in/casey-ross-a99152298?trk=public_post-text) + [Kelvin Byrd](https://www.linkedin.com/in/kelvin-byrd-med?trk=public_post-text) + [Raymond L. James, MSHE](https://www.linkedin.com/in/raymond-l-james-mshe-b438533a?trk=public_post-text) + [Terrance Shearn](https://www.linkedin.com/in/terrance-shearn-7a4547298?trk=public_post-text) + [Michelle McCallum](https://www.linkedin.com/in/michelle-mccallum-7b140b2b?trk=public_post-text)\n    \n    …more\n    \n       [154](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fposts%2Fagardner22_constructioninclusionweek-womentalkconstruction-activity-7384692628832821248-qPPp&trk=public_post_social-actions-reactions) [3 Comments](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fposts%2Fagardner22_constructioninclusionweek-womentalkconstruction-activity-7384692628832821248-qPPp&trk=public_post_social-actions-comments)\n    \n    [Like](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fposts%2Fagardner22_constructioninclusionweek-womentalkconstruction-activity-7384692628832821248-qPPp&trk=public_post_like-cta) [Comment](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fposts%2Fagardner22_constructioninclusionweek-womentalkconstruction-activity-7384692628832821248-qPPp&trk=public_post_comment-cta)\n    \n    Share\n    \n    *   Copy\n    *   LinkedIn\n    *   Facebook\n    *   X\n    \n    To view or add a comment, [sign in](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fposts%2Fagardner22_constructioninclusionweek-womentalkconstruction-activity-7384692628832821248-qPPp&trk=public_post_feed-cta-banner-cta)\n    \n*   [](https://www.linkedin.com/posts/jtm-construction_onejtm-constructioninclusionweek2025-activity-7383558020968079360-Qb0_)\n    \n     [](https://www.linkedin.com/company/jtm-construction?trk=public_post_feed-actor-image)\n    \n    [JTM Construction](https://www.linkedin.com/company/jtm-construction?trk=public_post_feed-actor-name)\n    \n    6,496 followers\n    \n    5mo Edited\n    \n    *   [Report this post](/uas/login?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fposts%