t and leadership pathways (on and off the tools) - Workplace culture and retention Register at [https://lnkd.in/gHpWZD9d](https://www.linkedin.com/redir/redirect?url=https%3A%2F%2Flnkd%2Ein%2FgHpWZD9d&urlhash=iSnN&trk=public_post-text). [#construction](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fhashtag%2Fconstruction&trk=public_post-text) [#WomenInConstruction](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fhashtag%2Fwomeninconstruction&trk=public_post-text) [Richard Lyall, ICD.D, MA, CAE](https://ca.linkedin.com/in/richardlyall?trk=public_post-text) [Andrew Pariser](https://ca.linkedin.com/in/andrew-pariser-14978215?trk=public_post-text) [Meredith Greaves](https://ca.linkedin.com/in/meredithgreaves?trk=public_post-text) [Yasmin Bond](https://ca.linkedin.com/in/yasmin-bond?trk=public_post-text)\n    \n    *    \n    \n     [11](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fposts%2Frescon-residential-construction-council-of-ontario_construction-womeninconstruction-activity-7384670783522062337-JD9h&trk=public_post_social-actions-reactions) [1 Comment](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fposts%2Frescon-residential-construction-council-of-ontario_construction-womeninconstruction-activity-7384670783522062337-JD9h&trk=public_post_social-actions-comments)\n    \n    [Like](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fposts%2Frescon-residential-construction-council-of-ontario_construction-womeninconstruction-activity-7384670783522062337-JD9h&trk=public_post_like-cta) [Comment](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fposts%2Frescon-residential-construction-council-of-ontario_construction-womeninconstruction-activity-7384670783522062337-JD9h&trk=public_post_comment-cta)\n    \n    Share\n    \n    *   Copy\n    *   LinkedIn\n    *   Facebook\n    *   X\n    \n    To view or add a comment, [sign in](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fposts%2Frescon-residential-construction-council-of-ontario_construction-womeninconstruction-activity-7384670783522062337-JD9h&trk=public_post_feed-cta-banner-cta)\n    \n*   [](https://www.linkedin.com/posts/rkindustriesllc_rkindustries-constructioninclusionweek-activity-7383501899573944320-e2CW)\n    \n     [](https://www.linkedin.com/company/rkindustriesllc?trk=public_post_feed-actor-image)\n    \n    [RK](https://www.linkedin.com/company/rkindustriesllc?trk=public_post_feed-actor-name)\n    \n    22,133 followers\n    \n    5mo\n    \n    *   [Report this post](/uas/login?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fposts%2Frkindustriesllc_rkindustries-constructioninclusionweek-activity-7383501899573944320-e2CW&trk=public_post_ellipsis-menu-semaphore-sign-in-redirect&guestReportContentType=POST&_f=guest-reporting)\n    \n    It’s Construction Inclusion Week! This year’s theme, Opening Doors: Building a Workplace for Everyone, challenges our industry to do more than just build projects. It calls on us to build cultures where belonging is real, opportunities are clear and respect is non-negotiable. Diversity is central to attracting and retaining the next generation of skilled trade professionals. By creating pathways for people of every background, we strengthen not only our company, but the communities we serve. We’re proud to stand with our peers across the country in advancing the future of construction. [#RKIndustries](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fhashtag%2Frkindustries&trk=public_post-text) [#ConstructionInclusionWeek](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fhashtag%2Fconstructioninclusionweek&trk=public_post-text) [#CareersInConstruction](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fhashtag%2Fcareersinconstruction&trk=public_post-text) [#InclusiveWorkforce](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fhashtag%2Finclusiveworkforce&trk=public_post-text) [#SkilledTrades](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fhashtag%2Fskilledtrades&trk=public_post-text) [#BuildYourFuture](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fhashtag%2Fbuildyourfuture&trk=public_post-text)\n    \n    *    \n    \n     [18](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fposts%2Frkindustriesllc_rkindustries-constructioninclusionweek-activity-7383501899573944320-e2CW&trk=public_post_social-actions-reactions)\n    \n    [Like](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fposts%2Frkindustriesllc_rkindustries-constructioninclusionweek-activity-7383501899573944320-e2CW&trk=public_post_like-cta) [Comment](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fposts%2Frkindustriesllc_rkindustries-constructioninclusionweek-activity-7383501899573944320-e2CW&trk=public_post_comment-cta)\n    \n    Share\n    \n    *   Copy\n    *   LinkedIn\n    *   Facebook\n    *   X\n    \n    To view or add a comment, [sign in](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fposts%2Frkindustriesllc_rkindustries-constructioninclusionweek-activity-7383501899573944320-e2CW&trk=public_post_feed-cta-banner-cta)\n    \n*   [](https://www.linkedin.com/posts/wates_womeninconstruction-wiceawards2025-allyship-activity-7378711328460394496-RL4y)\n    \n     [](https://uk.linkedin.com/company/wates?trk=public_post_feed-actor-image)\n    \n    [Wates Group](https://uk.linkedin.com/company/wates?trk=public_post_feed-actor-name)\n    \n    182,825 followers\n    \n    6mo Edited\n    \n    *   [Report this post](/uas/login?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fposts%2Fwates_womeninconstruction-wiceawards2025-allyship-activity-7378711328460394496-RL4y&trk=public_post_ellipsis-menu-semaphore-sign-in-redirect&guestReportContentType=POST&_f=guest-reporting)\n    \n    We were proud to be represented by Executive Managing Director Steffan Battle, at this year’s [Design and Build UK](https://uk.linkedin.com/company/designandbuilduk?trk=public_post-text) Women in Construction Awards – an evening dedicated to recognising the incredible achievements of women across our industry. Steff’s keynote speech focused on the importance of allyship – not just in words, but in daily actions. He reflected on the progress made, the challenges that remain, and the role men must play in driving change. At Wates, we’re committed to building a business where women can thrive. That means: • Five women on our Executive Committee • Reverse mentoring programmes • Inclusive parental leave • A growing graduate intake approaching gender parity We’re also proud to partner with [Premiership Women's Rugby](https://uk.linkedin.com/company/premiership-women-s-rugby?trk=public_post-text), because we believe the same principles apply in sport and construction: when you invest in women, they thrive, as the Red Roses just proved with their incredible World Cup victory. Steff also highlighted the powerful impact of Building Women by Faye Allen – a must-read for anyone in the industry, especially male allies. The stories shared in that book are a reminder of why inclusion matters and why we must keep pushing for better. To every nominee and winner – congratulations. You’re already changing the game. Let’s keep building a future where every woman in construction can thrive. Find out more about how we’re cultivating a supportive and inclusive workplace: [https://lnkd.in/e2NsYBiS](https://www.linkedin.com/redir/redirect?url=https%3A%2F%2Flnkd%2Ein%2Fe2NsYBiS&urlhash=CCjh&trk=public_post-text) [#WomenInConstruction](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fhashtag%2Fwomeninconstruction&trk=public_post-text) [#WICEAwards2025](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fhashtag%2Fwiceawards2025&trk=public_post-text) [#Allyship](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fhashtag%2Fallyship&trk=public_post-text) [#Inclusion](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fhashtag%2Finclusion&trk=public_post-text) [#Diversity](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fhashtag%2Fdiversity&trk=public_post-text) [#Leadership](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fhashtag%2Fleadership&trk=public_post-text) [#ThriveTogether](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fhashtag%2Fthrivetogether&trk=public_post-text) [#ThrivingPeople](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fhashtag%2Fthrivingpeople&trk=public_post-text)\n    \n    *    \n    \n       [161](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fposts%2Fwates_womeninconstruction-wiceawards2025-allyship-activity-7378711328460394496-RL4y&trk=public_post_social-actions-reactions) [4 Comments](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fposts%2Fwates_womeninconstruction-wiceawards2025-allyship-activity-7378711328460394496-RL4y&trk=public_post_social-actions-comments)\n    \n    [Like](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fposts%2Fwates_womeninconstruction-wiceawards2025-allyship-activity-7378711328460394496-RL4y&trk=public_post_like-cta) [Comment](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fposts%2Fwates_womeninconstruction-wiceawards2025-allyship-activity-7378711328460394496-RL4y&trk=public_post_comment-cta)\n    \n    Share\n    \n    *   Copy\n    *   LinkedIn\n    *   Facebook\n    *   X\n    \n    To view or add a comment, [sign in](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fposts%2Fwates_womeninconstruction-wiceawards2025-allyship-activity-7378711328460394496-RL4y&trk=public_post_feed-cta-banner-cta)\n    \n*   [](https://www.linkedin.com/posts/chicago-women-in-trades_careersinconstructionmonth-cwitstories-activity-7384226993292312576-NTfD)\n    \n     [](https://www.linkedin.com/company/chicago-women-in-trades?trk=public_post_feed-actor-image)\n    \n    [Chicago Women in Trades](https://www.linkedin.com/company/chicago-women-in-trades?trk=public_post_feed-actor-name)\n    \n    2,876 followers\n    \n    5mo\n    \n    *   [Report this post](/uas/login?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fposts%2Fchicago-women-in-trades_careersinconstructionmonth-cwitstories-activity-7384226993292312576-NTfD&trk=public_post_ellipsis-menu-semaphore-sign-in-redirect&guestReportContentType=POST&_f=guest-reporting)\n    \n    This Construction Inclusion Week, Illinois has the chance to send a clear message: diversity is our strength, and our workforce should reflect it. Despite representing nearly 50% of the workforce, women make up less than 5% of construction workers. Federal initiatives that increased access to high-wage construction careers are under attack. HR 161 calls on Illinois to adopt strong policies that protect workers from harassment and discrimination and create equal access to job opportunities on safe, respectful, accountable worksites. Contact your state representative and urge them to co-sponsor HR 161. Link to: [https://lnkd.in/gHmsPZ3T](https://www.linkedin.com/redir/redirect?url=https%3A%2F%2Flnkd%2Ein%2FgHmsPZ3T&urlhash=xDdB&trk=public_post-text) [#CareersInConstructionMonth](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fhashtag%2Fcareersinconstructionmonth&trk=public_post-text) [#CWITStories](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fhashtag%2Fcwitstories&trk=public_post-text) [#Tradeswomen](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fhashtag%2Ftradeswomen&trk=public_post-text) [#CWIT](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fhashtag%2Fcwit&trk=public_post-text) [#ChicagoWomenInTrades](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fhashtag%2Fchicagowomenintrades&trk=public_post-text) [#ConstructionInclusionWeek](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fhashtag%2Fconstructioninclusionweek&trk=public_post-text) [#HR161](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fhashtag%2Fhr161&trk=public_post-text)\n    \n    *    \n    \n       [49](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fposts%2Fchicago-women-in-trades_careersinconstructionmonth-cwitstories-activity-7384226993292312576-NTfD&trk=public_post_social-actions-reactions)\n    \n    [Like](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fposts%2Fchicago-women-in-trades_careersinconstructionmonth-cwitstories-activity-7384226993292312576-NTfD&trk=public_post_like-cta) [Comment](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2